args:
The prince and his friends arrive at the foot of
the Sacred Tree and discover the collapsed
bodies of the faeries tasked with protecting it.
Having taken down its protective barrier,
Nedrick and Jinlorda are already ascending
the tree, and our heroes take off in pursuit.
(We've gone so far, yet the top seems\nas far away as when we first started.\nHow large is this tree, anyway?)
(Also, why have we been tarrying at this\nspot for so long now?)
(Ah! I am certain I heard him mention the\nseventh scion!)
(Could my brother have come here to the\nSacred Tree?)
How shall we proceed, King Jinlorda?
What think you, Nedrick? It seems the\nseventh scion's group will arrive soon.
I've already taken steps. We don't need to\ndo anything else.
In that case, I'll leave the matter be.\nAnd what of the guardians?
They are no match for us and the power\nof metamorphosis.
How fragile a thing is a civilization mired\nin tradition and neglectful of progress.
That body of yours never changes, does it?
(Was that mana that went into his body\njust now?!)
(He absorbed the mana of the Sacred Tree?\nWhat is he doing?)
We set out from Finlorda's manor, made our\nway out of the forest of the Faerie Kingdom,\nand proceeded due north.
Notte knew exactly where to go, so we made\nsteady progress before finally arriving at the\nbase of the Sacred Tree.
So this is the Sacred Tree.
No wonder we could see it from such a\ngreat distance...

And it's got mana oozin' out its...pores or
whatever trees have. Hell, even I can
sense it, and I usually don't know squat
about that kinda stuff.
It is as if my body threatens to be overrun\nwith mana simply by standing here.
And my father's thoughts are waiting for\nme somewhere...
Your Majesty, someone is fallen there!
It's a faerie! Oh man, this looks bad...
I have made the rounds, Your Majesty,\nand beheld naught but utter devastation.
Those jerks took down all the Sacred Tree\nguardians! Every single one!
We may have been too late to help, but\nwe can do something now. ...Zena?
I will heal him at once, Brother.
We've come here at the request of the\nformer king, Finlorda.
King Finlorda...? Yes, of course.\nThe messenger.
Looks like Jinlorda and Nedrick thrashed\nyou folks good.
You have the right of it, sir. While their\nnumbers were few, they were strengthened\nwith the power of metamorphosis.
They destroyed the barrier put in place by\nwe guardians as if it were mere gossamer.
Jinlorda's supposed to be the king of this\nplace, and instead he's attacking his own\npeople? Ooo, that makes me furious!
Rage can wait, Mym. Right now, let's hurry\nand heal all the fallen we can.
Yeah! I'm sure we'll have 'em patched up\nin no time if we pitch in together!
Wait, please. I can heal my comrades.\nSo rather than worrying after us, I would\nhave you pursue the two invaders.

We faeries have protected the Sacred Tree
for generations upon generations. It is an
inviolable sanctuary, even for our long line
of royalty.
None can be permitted to make use of its\npower for personal gain.
And that is to say nothing of what might\nhappen if they manage to get their hands\non a sacred shard.
Please, I implore you! You must stop them!
You mustn't lose sight of your original\npurpose, {player_name}.
As this man says, now is the time to act\nin service of greater goals.
I can't stand the idea of leaving wounded\nbehind, but we don't have another choice.
Well, too bad I slept through lumberjack\nschool, 'cause I got no idea how we're\ngonna climb this thing.
First, follow the branches and proceed\nalong the lower strata.
Deep within you will find the Cloudbough,\nand from there you can access the canopy\nwhich leads to the upper stratum.

Exercise all due caution. The native
creatures who dwell in the tree are now
filled with rage over the invaders who
seek to ravage their home.
You just leave everything to me and\nmy darling!
Thank you for all your counsel, good faerie.\nAll right, everyone. We're heading up,\nso be on your guard and step lightly.
